---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGrid from "../../components/RelatedGrid.astro";

const relatedItems = [
  { kicker: "GUIDES", title: "Class Guide — All 8 Classes Compared", href: "/getting-started/class-guide/" },
  { kicker: "BUILDS", title: "Build Tier List", href: "/builds/tier-list/" },
  { kicker: "TOOLS", title: "Build Planner", href: "/build-planner/" },
  { kicker: "MECHANICS", title: "Passive Skill Tree Explained", href: "/mechanics/passive-tree/" },
  { kicker: "REFERENCE", title: "Skill Gems, Support Gems & Spirit Gems", href: "/skill-gems/" },
  { kicker: "REFERENCE", title: "Trade Guide", href: "/trade-guide/" },
];
---
<SiteLayout
  title="PoE2 Beginner Guide — Getting Started"
  description="New to Path of Exile 2? Start here: picking a class, understanding gems and the passive tree, and what to prioritize in your first playthrough."
>
  <h1>Getting Started with Path of Exile 2</h1>
  <p class="intro">
    PoE2 throws a lot at new players at once. This page is the on-ramp — read this first,
    then branch out into the deeper guides linked at the bottom.
  </p>

  <h2>Picking a class</h2>
  <p>
    Every class can eventually go in multiple directions once you pick an Ascendancy, so don't
    overthink your first choice, the starting attribute focus matters less than it looks like
    it should. Our <a href="/getting-started/class-guide/">full Class Guide</a> compares all 8
    classes side by side. If you want the lowest-friction start, our <a href="/builds/tier-list/">Build Tier List</a>
    flags which current builds are rated as good league starters specifically.
  </p>

  <h2>Understanding gems before you touch the skill panel</h2>
  <p>
    Skills in PoE2 are tied to your <strong>weapon</strong>, not your class — a big change from
    the original Path of Exile if you're coming from there. You won't find finished gems as
    drops; you'll find Uncut Gems that you turn into a specific skill yourself. Read the full
    <a href="/skill-gems/">skill gem breakdown</a> before you start making choices you'll want to undo.
  </p>

  <h2>The passive tree: don't panic</h2>
  <p>
    The tree looks overwhelming at first glance. The practical version: pick one Keystone as
    your anchor before you start allocating points, path toward Notables rather than detouring
    for small passives, and don't worry about "wasting" points early — respeccing costs Gold,
    not real money, and the cost only gets steep at higher levels. Full details on the
    <a href="/mechanics/passive-tree/">passive tree page</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Currency and trading, in one paragraph</h2>
  <p>
    You'll accumulate orbs constantly — don't hoard them out of caution. Chaos Orbs and Exalted
    Orbs are your everyday spending money; Divine Orbs are for expensive purchases. When you're
    ready to actually buy or sell gear, the <a href="/trade-guide/">trade guide</a> covers the
    three trading systems and how not to get scammed.
  </p>

  <h2>What to actually prioritize in your first playthrough</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Follow your build guide's leveling section rather than freestyling the passive tree — most wasted points happen in the first 20 levels.</li>
    <li>Don't skip side content that grants passive skill points or Weapon Set Passive Skill Points — they add up to real power over a full campaign.</li>
    <li>Pick up an Uncut Gem stash habit early — having spares on hand saves you from being stuck with a skill you don't like.</li>
    <li>Don't feel pressured to understand the trade site on day one — the campaign is fully completable on found gear.</li>
  </ul>

  <RelatedGrid items={relatedItems} heading="Where to go next" />
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .intro { color: var(--text-dim); max-width: 640px; }
  p { color: var(--text-dim); line-height: 1.75; }
  ul { color: var(--text-dim); }
</style>
